<subSubSection id="4A5A1699DDBF524EF13DC19757C57AB3" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="CD8C07FAD2470F48C4FAD6D65B7986CE" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D6B7DADACA3A47FD05674FCDF3FC7448" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Known only from the type locality. The plants grow in the entrances of limestone caves or moist cliffs of hill sides.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A83D488A580854A135870EDD14EE029F" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="567BBD9CE2CBA7C9BD92CFB7A8725B4D" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0A95348C48C2DC94C1D2E764D2D5152F" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Flowering in May-June and fruiting in June-August.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="82FEDD3011A2EE97C85ADB57EFF5F6AF" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="541BEC4C8B1FF0E860F755808B1187B4" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BF474DC938972AE15AEC0E7743DAE993" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">
The number of 
<taxonomicName id="6B85688042793D5456AFA71EFA23EEEE" authorityName="R. J. Wang" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spiradiclis longanensis" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longanensis">
<emphasis id="9310FB5494B5FA7C343D823A4DF03874" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Spiradiclis longanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was less than 500 individuals within an area of less than 5 km2; however we know that the present field investigation is in a very low density and the evaluation we made here was based on all the available information up to now. We therefore assign a preliminary IUCN threat status of Vulnerable (VU, B2ab(ii, iii, iv); D) to 
<taxonomicName id="9E6E4DEABD6748D707204C9AD42A1D17" authorityName="R. J. Wang" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spiradiclis longanensis" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longanensis">
<emphasis id="CEABD912C89F4C2583CD24AF850AE9BF" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Spiradiclis longanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="80CFE20D911BAAFFDA04BFAD96C6C99D" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN Species Survival Commission. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland" pageId="3" pageNumber="116" refId="B5" refString="IUCN, 2001. IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. IUCN Species Survival Commission. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland" title="IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1" year="2001">IUCN 2001</bibRefCitation>
). The populations are probably prone to the effects of human activities or stochastic events in future, because the plants grow nearby the main traffic road or rice field.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
