</taxonomicName>
in this genus, 
<taxonomicName id="7480F3E14BBBE71DB3627626EB11A7D8" authorityName="R. J. Wang" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spiradiclis danxiashanensis" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="danxiashanensis">
<emphasis id="A97ADDB0EBF2409AC4A2A1199D8E7FCA" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Spiradiclis danxiashanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="99FDCBD08238414EBD3ECE46373ACAD5" authorityName="H. S. Lo" authorityYear="1987" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spiradiclis guangdongensis" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="guangdongensis">
<emphasis id="562BE21BA66B05891F95FB44CE2403A9" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Spiradiclis guangdongensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="CCFF77FD6CFD5B5CB86484B7452816F4" authorityName="H. S. Lo" authorityYear="1987" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spiradiclis hainanensis" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hainanensis">
<emphasis id="1A30CAC5B2D6F790A5366A1649B1ADCC" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Spiradiclis hainanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="7C62B4EA1A7479C8AEE142B56ABA239E" authorityName="H. S. Lo" authorityYear="1986" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spiradiclis umbelliformis" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="umbelliformis">
<emphasis id="5CC0119F27018B01D29962A36AF54006" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Spiradiclis umbelliformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are all in prostrate or decumbent habit, but their leaf laminas, inflorescences, calyx lobes, and flowers are different from 
<taxonomicName id="03EF880185CD528CF33A5CE8C7FA8207" authorityName="R. J. Wang" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Spiradiclis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Spiradiclis longanensis" order="Gentianales" pageId="2" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="longanensis">
<emphasis id="E6BAA2583963BC34C23BF619B1B3F41D" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="115">Spiradiclis longanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and can easily be distinguished. The latter four species usually have rounded, orbicular, or ovate leaf laminas in 1-2.5 mm long and with 3-5 unobvious secondary veins each side, and their inflorescences often include 1-3 salverform and never condensed flowers, with ovate to lanceolate calyx lobes.
</paragraph>
